March 17, 2019

Ideation

Suicide is an international plague which impacts not only the victim, but the family and friends of the victim. What if we could use data science to help predict people at risk of suicide to target mental health resources?

Data Used

The data used for this work was found on the Kaggle website: https://www.kaggle.com/russellyates88/suicide-rates-overview-1985-to-2016#master.csv

It contains data from 1985 to 2016 with socio-economic information with suicide rates by year and country. The ultimate sources of the information compiled on the Kaggle website follow:

  • United Nations Development Program.
  • World Bank
  • Suicide in the Twenty-First Century (also on Kaggle)
  • World Health Organization

Architecture

The architecture for my work on this project is relatively simple. I don't have access to Visio, so I was unable to draw a nice picture. However, the following was done from an architectural standpoint:

  • Retrieve .csv file from the internet
  • Pull in .csv file into Rstudio
  • Pull in .csv file into Microsoft Power BI
  • Extract data from Rstudio into excel for massaging, then reimport into RStudio

Data Analysis

Use Microsoft Power BI to get a sense of the impact of Countries and age on the Suicide rates.

Decision Tree

Use decision tree with cross fold validation with 70% - 30% split between training and testing data

  • 10 fold
  • Use Information Gain Criterion
  • Use Gini Criterion
